==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Budge
<hw>Budge</hw> <pr>(b⟦ucr⟧j)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Budged</conjf> <pr>(b⟦ucr⟧jd)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Budging</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[F. <ets>bouger</ets> to
stir, move (akin to Pr. <ets>bojar</ets>, <ets>bolegar</ets>, to stir,
move, It. <ets>bulicare</ets> to boil, bubble), fr. L.
<ets>bullire</ets>. See <er>Boil</er>, <pos>v. i.</pos>]</ety> <def>To
move off; to stir; to walk away.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>I'll not <qex>budge</qex> an inch, boy.</q>
<rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The mouse ne'er shunned the cat as they did <qex>budge</qex>⟦br⟧
From rascals worse than they.</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Budge</ent>⟦br⟧

